name: Kuttikar Bar And Restaurant

reviews.review_text:
DownTown Low Key Restaurant for seafood options.

In my opinion this would be the best sea food in Goa.

I even doubt that any 5 Star will have such a great taste.

Try the Red Sniper and Tiger Prawns/Normal Prawns. They are awesome.

A wonderful place if you live fish. We ordered for some kingfish rava fry, xinanyo rava fry and bombil fry. Everything was so fresh and authentically made. The taste was amazing. The prawns curry we had with rice was also nice. Not great as I like my humann to be slightly on the spicier side. But many people do not want the spice. So that's okay! The waiter was also a very friendly chap named Prem who did not make us wait for too long even though it was the rush hour during lunch time. Overall a wonderful experience. Would definitely visit again! Keep up the good work Kuttikar restaurant team, please keep the quality same! Best wishes!

This place is a gem only locals know.
If you love seafood and are in old goa, you must dine at kuttikar.
It doesn't look much from the outside but don't let it's appearance fool you.

They have a wide range of seafood delicacy that will leave your mouth watering.
Ps don't go on Sundays ðŸ˜‚
Locals seem to love it with regular customer everytime.
Friendly staff and super refreshing seafood
